{"lemma":"اِشْتِقاقُ","slug":"اِشْتِقاقُ","root":"ش.ق.ق","root_slug":"ش-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22696"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%90%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of اِشْتَقَّ (ištaqqa) (form VIII)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"etymology, derivation"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/iʃ.ti.qaːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22696","headword_ar":"اِشْتِقَاقٌ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing, (S, K,) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (S.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tq~ Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"اشتقّ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deriving"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a word"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a word, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the condition of reciprocal relation in meaning and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radical"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composition, and of reciprocal difference in form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and it is of three kinds:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAi$otiqaAqu AlS~agiyru","text_ar":"الاِشْتِقَاقُ الصَّغِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that derivation in which there is a reciprocal relation between the two words in the letters and in the order"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~arobu","text_ar":"الضَّرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA$tqAq Alkabiyru","text_ar":"الاشتقاق الكَبِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that in which there is a reciprocal relation between the two words as to the letter and the meaning, exclusively of the order; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaba*a","text_ar":"جَبَذَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alja*obu","text_ar":"الجَذْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA$tqAq AlA^akobaru","text_ar":"الاشتقاق الاَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that in which there is a reciprocal relation between the two words in the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of utterance; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEaqa","text_ar":"نَعَقَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ahoqu","text_ar":"النَّهْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KT.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tq~","text_ar":"اشتقّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarofFA","text_ar":"حَرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimapF","text_ar":"كَلِمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZFA","text_ar":"لَفْظًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@somFA","text_ar":"ا@سْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He derived a word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a name,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A=xara","text_ar":"مِنْ ا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~ahu","text_ar":"شَقَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes signifies the same, as is shown by a citation voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHimN","text_ar":"رَحِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [And, as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixotiraAEN","text_ar":"اِخْتِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see 8 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrE","text_ar":"خرع"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constructing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"founding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bunoyaAn","text_ar":"بُنْيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, what is originated without premeditation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking to the right and left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not pursuing the right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direct, course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) in speech, and in contention, or disputation, or litigation: (S, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otiqaAqu AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"اِشْتِقَاقُ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the taking to the right and left in speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in a copy of the M: [but I think that the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAi$otiqaAqu fiY AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"الاِشْتِقَاقُ فِى الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with what here follows:]) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tq~ fiY AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"اشتقّ فِى الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlxuSuwmapi","text_ar":"فِى الخُصُومَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) See also 6. And [in like manner] one says of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tq~ fiY Eadowihi","text_ar":"اشتقّ فِى عَدْوِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to the right and left in his running."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aq~u","text_ar":"اَشَقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tq~ AlT~ariyqu fiY AlfalaApi","text_ar":"اشتقّ الطَّرِيقُ فِى الفَلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The road went"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branched off"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the desert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also 7.])"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}